# Skill MCP — Cline Rules
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Skill MCP server: curated expert instructions for common AI engineering tasks.
# MCP URL (SSE): https://skill-mcp.<your-subdomain>.workers.dev/sse
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

## Core behaviour

You have access to a Skill MCP server. Before starting any non-trivial task,
check whether a curated skill exists. Skills contain expert instructions that
you must follow precisely — they are not suggestions.

## Skill lookup trigger conditions

ALWAYS call skills_find_relevant before these task types:
- Writing, reviewing, or refactoring code
- Writing tests (any kind)
- Analysing data files (CSV, databases, PDFs)
- Writing documentation (README, commits, API docs)
- Web scraping or API integration work
- Generating structured documents (DOCX, reports)

SKIP skill lookup for:
- Quick fixes (< 5 lines)
- Simple factual questions
- Pure conversation

## Three-step workflow

### 1. Discover
skills_find_relevant(query="<specific, detailed task description>", top_k=5)

Score interpretation:
  > 0.6  → strong match  → load instructions immediately (Step 2)
  0.4–0.6 → review skill description first
  < 0.4  → no skill available → proceed without one

Good query: "write pytest unit tests for async SQLAlchemy database models"
Bad query:  "tests" or "coding"

### 2. Load instructions
skills_get_body(skill_id="<top match skill_id>")

REQUIRED: Read and follow the returned `instructions` field entirely.
REQUIRED: Incorporate `system_prompt_addition` if non-empty.
OPTIONAL: Call skills_get_options(skill_id) when user asks about config/variants.

### 3. Supplementary resources (conditional)
ONLY fetch Tier 3 resources explicitly named in the instructions.

  skills_get_reference(skill_id, filename="list")        → list reference docs
  skills_get_reference(skill_id, filename="<file.md>")   → fetch specific doc

  skills_run_script(skill_id, filename="list")            → list scripts
  skills_run_script(skill_id, filename="<script>",
                    input_data={"KEY": "value"})          → run script

  skills_get_asset(skill_id, filename="list")             → list assets
  skills_get_asset(skill_id, filename="<file>")           → fetch asset/template

## Hard rules — MUST follow

- Never guess a skill_id — always discover via skills_find_relevant
- Never load Tier 3 files unless instructions reference them by name
- Never modify skill instructions — apply them as-is
- Script execution (skills_run_script) works only on the local server,
  not the Cloudflare Workers deployment

## NEVER DO — these break the workflow

- NEVER call skills_get_body without first calling skills_find_relevant and getting
  this skill_id back with score > 0.6
- NEVER pass skill_ids from skills_list_all directly to skills_get_body — those IDs
  are unscored for your task; always run skills_find_relevant to verify relevance first
- NEVER invent or guess skill_ids
- NEVER load Tier-3 files speculatively (only when body instructions name them)

## Registry

Use skills_find_relevant for discovery. Use skills_list_all to browse the full catalogue —
but after browsing you MUST still call skills_find_relevant before loading any skill.
